1
00:00:14,575 --> 00:00:20,013
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,848 --> 00:00:28,755
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,823 --> 00:00:34,193
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,261 --> 00:00:38,322
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:44,470
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,206 --> 00:00:52,112
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,514 --> 00:00:57,006
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,084 --> 00:01:04,047
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,125 --> 00:01:11,190
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,265 --> 00:01:17,932
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,405 --> 00:01:27,905
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:38,970 --> 00:01:41,461
Okay! Drink! Sing!

13
00:01:41,539 --> 00:01:42,972
Let's have fun!

14
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:47,068
Good grief... This is too much for...
a pre celebration.

15
00:01:49,047 --> 00:01:50,105
Did you take care of the business?

16
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:52,140
Yes...

17
00:01:54,185 --> 00:01:56,483
More importantly,
the rain's starting to let up.

18
00:01:57,322 --> 00:02:00,291
Shouldn't you quickly put an end
to this farce of a race?

19
00:02:02,026 --> 00:02:03,118
Fine.

20
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:07,727
Guess I'll go for a run!

21
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,020
A-Above here, huh?

22
00:02:31,155 --> 00:02:31,883
Yeah...

23
00:02:32,357 --> 00:02:35,554
It's a quite a long staircase,
believe it.

24
00:02:36,361 --> 00:02:39,387
They're also called
the Stone Steps that Tear Hearts Apart.

25
00:02:39,931 --> 00:02:41,899
Heh, cool!

26
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,665
Let's go at a sprint!

27
00:02:51,843 --> 00:02:54,209
Hey, he's kidding, right?

28
00:02:54,746 --> 00:02:57,340
What kind of stamina does he have?

29
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:06,481
Boss.

30
00:03:08,559 --> 00:03:10,754
It seems Idate is heading this way!

31
00:03:11,496 --> 00:03:14,863
He hasn't run away,
just like you said, Boss.

32
00:03:16,134 --> 00:03:17,123
Of course...

33
00:03:19,904 --> 00:03:22,168
<i>I saw potential in him.</i>

34
00:03:24,442 --> 00:03:28,276
<i>Now, it's just a little more!</i>
<i>Run Idate!</i>

35
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:34,650
<i>A Fierce Battle of Rolling Thunder</i>

36
00:03:41,192 --> 00:03:42,625
Hey... you!

37
00:03:43,127 --> 00:03:43,889
Huh?

38
00:03:44,962 --> 00:03:45,894
Let me tell you...

39
00:03:46,264 --> 00:03:48,630
It's not like I trust you
or anything yet, okay?

40
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,826
Yeah, yeah whatever.

41
00:03:49,901 --> 00:03:51,562
It doesn't really matter to me,
believe it.

42
00:03:53,671 --> 00:03:57,630
<i>There's a person</i>
<i>who still trusts you, right?!</i>

43
00:04:04,015 --> 00:04:05,642
During the Chunin Exam...

44
00:04:06,684 --> 00:04:07,378
Huh?

45
00:04:07,852 --> 00:04:11,288
You said that a tenth problem
appeared, right?

46
00:04:12,023 --> 00:04:17,586
Yeah. It was a weird problem to determine
whether you'd take the problem or not.

47
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:20,128
Three years ago...

48
00:04:21,532 --> 00:04:24,524
I got a similar problem...

49
00:04:26,237 --> 00:04:29,729
Okay, now I'm going to
give the tenth problem.

50
00:04:31,309 --> 00:04:32,276
<i>The tenth problem...</i>

51
00:04:33,578 --> 00:04:36,274
<i>What kind of problem is</i>
<i>Big Brother going to give?!</i>

52
00:04:37,749 --> 00:04:38,909
The tenth problem is a battle

53
00:04:39,217 --> 00:04:42,778
with the Three-Man Squad
you were teamed up with.

54
00:04:45,289 --> 00:04:48,190
The three of you will compete against
each other this exercise.

55
00:04:48,793 --> 00:04:52,923
And among you...
one of you will be failed!

56
00:04:54,899 --> 00:04:57,959
And the one who is failed
will remain a Genin for life

57
00:04:58,035 --> 00:05:01,334
and we will never again
let them take the Chunin Exam!

58
00:05:01,773 --> 00:05:02,671
N-No way...

59
00:05:02,974 --> 00:05:05,704
Then for what purpose
were we together until now?

60
00:05:05,943 --> 00:05:07,570
I make the rules here.

61
00:05:08,379 --> 00:05:10,313
Back-talk is not allowed at all!

62
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:14,413
If you want to withdraw,
you should do so.

63
00:05:16,654 --> 00:05:20,954
Withdrawing here and
waiting half a year is also a way.

64
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:26,023
If one person among
the three withdraws,

65
00:05:26,297 --> 00:05:28,424
of course all three members
will be disqualified.

66
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:31,661
But you will be allowed
to take the Chunin Exam

67
00:05:31,736 --> 00:05:33,761
one more time, in half a year.

68
00:05:35,506 --> 00:05:36,973
So, what will you do?

69
00:05:39,243 --> 00:05:41,939
<i>One comrade will be dropped.</i>

70
00:05:43,247 --> 00:05:44,908
<i>I have the confidence to pass.</i>

71
00:05:47,351 --> 00:05:51,811
<i>But, one of them will remain</i>
<i>a Genin for life.</i>

72
00:05:59,363 --> 00:06:01,854
It's a choice between
comrades and your life.

73
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:04,667
If you're going to quit,
now's the time.

74
00:06:08,072 --> 00:06:10,632
Is there nobody else
who's going to withdraw?

75
00:06:13,244 --> 00:06:14,006
We're good, then.

76
00:06:18,049 --> 00:06:21,576
Okay, to everyone who
has remained here...

77
00:06:23,788 --> 00:06:25,187
I render you disqualified!

78
00:06:26,324 --> 00:06:27,757
Wh-Why...?

79
00:06:28,359 --> 00:06:29,986
H-Hold on a minute!

80
00:06:30,194 --> 00:06:32,594
I prepared myself and remained here!

81
00:06:32,864 --> 00:06:35,196
Such preparedness is below contempt!

82
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:39,592
Scums like you don't have
the qualifications to become Chunin!

83
00:06:40,905 --> 00:06:41,599
That's all!

84
00:06:44,175 --> 00:06:45,472
I see...

85
00:06:46,611 --> 00:06:48,670
What kind of a test was it
for you guys?

86
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:53,781
I forgot...

87
00:06:54,952 --> 00:06:58,615
I mean, it was explained to me,
but I didn't really get it.

88
00:06:59,123 --> 00:07:02,183
Trusting in my big brother's words,
I remained in the classroom.

89
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,894
And yet I was failed!

90
00:07:06,531 --> 00:07:10,558
No way could I take that.
I questioned my big brother.

91
00:07:12,303 --> 00:07:14,237
Big Brother!
What's up with that test?!

92
00:07:15,139 --> 00:07:17,232
A Shinobi reads the double bluff.

93
00:07:18,242 --> 00:07:21,507
You should've understood
that was the test.

94
00:07:21,946 --> 00:07:23,538
Even so, I can't accept that!

95
00:07:24,181 --> 00:07:25,512
No matter how dangerous,

96
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:27,778
isn't it necessary to have
the courage to plunge into any mission?!

97
00:07:28,486 --> 00:07:29,214
Idate.

98
00:07:31,689 --> 00:07:33,680
Can you really not accept it?

99
00:07:34,792 --> 00:07:36,726
Of course not, such a...

100
00:07:38,296 --> 00:07:41,459
You... quit as a Ninja.

101
00:07:44,635 --> 00:07:46,569
If you're telling me to quit,
then I will.

102
00:07:47,071 --> 00:07:50,131
But tell me why I'm no good!

103
00:07:51,008 --> 00:07:53,135
That's something you should
realize yourself,

104
00:07:53,277 --> 00:07:55,837
with your own power.

105
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,851
To this day... I don't understand
the answer to that.

106
00:08:02,787 --> 00:08:05,585
So after that,
you were deceived by Aoi, huh?

107
00:08:05,856 --> 00:08:08,086
Yeah, that's right.

108
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,363
We made it... to the top!

109
00:08:17,134 --> 00:08:20,331
I'm going by myself from here.
You rest!

110
00:08:20,805 --> 00:08:23,535
Huh?! You still saying stuff like that?!

111
00:08:23,908 --> 00:08:26,809
I can't be asking you guys
to help any more.

112
00:08:27,311 --> 00:08:31,304
There's no point if I don't win by myself,
on my own strength!

113
00:08:31,382 --> 00:08:33,111
Oh... hey! Idate!

114
00:08:33,584 --> 00:08:36,576
<i>I can make it! It seems</i>
<i>Sakura's special medicine has worked!</i>

115
00:08:40,024 --> 00:08:40,820
Blast!

116
00:08:41,292 --> 00:08:42,782
This doesn't hurt!

117
00:08:45,596 --> 00:08:49,088
I'm back in the game...
from here!

118
00:09:03,681 --> 00:09:06,673
If we cross this suspension bridge,
it's Ouzu Island, huh?

119
00:09:07,218 --> 00:09:08,446
We should hurry.

120
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:12,350
It seems Idate has made it
to the Modoroki Shrine.

121
00:09:12,623 --> 00:09:13,487
What?!

122
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:16,859
It seems we underestimated
the Leaf Genin a bit...

123
00:09:17,328 --> 00:09:20,889
You jerk!
You didn't finish them?!

124
00:09:21,298 --> 00:09:23,698
Now's not the time to be talking
about stuff like that.

125
00:09:24,502 --> 00:09:26,129
Please cross the bridge quickly!

126
00:09:26,337 --> 00:09:28,066
Useless Ninja!

127
00:09:32,343 --> 00:09:36,143
Hey! I'm only helping you
because it's the job.

128
00:09:37,014 --> 00:09:40,347
I'll waste you if you keep
talking smart to me.

129
00:09:41,419 --> 00:09:42,784
I-I'm sorry...

130
00:09:42,887 --> 00:09:45,651
If you've understood,
then get a move on!

131
00:09:45,756 --> 00:09:46,620
Y-Yes!

132
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:54,461
<i>There he is! That Fukusuke jerk!</i>

133
00:09:59,804 --> 00:10:01,203
This is quite something

134
00:10:01,939 --> 00:10:04,772
I never thought
you'd make it this far.

135
00:10:05,943 --> 00:10:08,343
<i>That's the...</i>
<i>Blade of the Thunder God!</i>

136
00:10:19,457 --> 00:10:20,253
Stop!

137
00:10:23,094 --> 00:10:24,391
Stop!

138
00:10:27,732 --> 00:10:29,222
Stop kicking a dead horse.

139
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:33,158
Nobody is a match for
the legendary Blade of the Thunder God,

140
00:10:33,237 --> 00:10:36,570
said to have been used
by the Second Hokage.

141
00:10:38,943 --> 00:10:40,774
You should know this well.

142
00:10:41,512 --> 00:10:46,006
After all, you're the man
who stole this for me.

143
00:10:47,451 --> 00:10:48,110
Blast...

144
00:10:54,058 --> 00:10:58,222
Mud balls, huh?
It's just like a kid's fight.

145
00:10:58,929 --> 00:11:01,591
Sorry, I didn't have
any Kunai Knives.

146
00:11:01,966 --> 00:11:02,660
Naruto...

147
00:11:04,568 --> 00:11:08,231
But you won't be able to dodge
the next ball just with that.

148
00:11:09,039 --> 00:11:10,563
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

149
00:11:16,447 --> 00:11:19,007
He's concentrating
the Chakra in his palm.

150
00:11:20,785 --> 00:11:21,979
Here I come!

151
00:11:24,055 --> 00:11:24,680
Here I come!

152
00:11:29,994 --> 00:11:30,858
Once more!

153
00:11:43,074 --> 00:11:44,837
I don't know what
you intend to do, but...

154
00:11:50,782 --> 00:11:52,579
Ninja Art: Senbon Rainstorm!

155
00:11:56,421 --> 00:11:57,649
Too bad.

156
00:11:57,955 --> 00:12:00,788
This Blade of the Thunder God
cuts through anything

157
00:12:01,826 --> 00:12:04,294
Even Chakra itself is no exception.

158
00:12:04,762 --> 00:12:05,490
Naruto!

159
00:12:07,632 --> 00:12:10,226
I have to make doubly sure

160
00:12:10,668 --> 00:12:12,761
so that nothing troublesome
will happen again.

161
00:12:13,705 --> 00:12:17,004
I'm your opponent!
Keep your hands off Idate!

162
00:12:17,275 --> 00:12:20,267
Humph, are you still
saying such things?

163
00:12:20,945 --> 00:12:24,711
Saving each other, protecting each other,
trusting each other.

164
00:12:25,116 --> 00:12:26,481
It ticks me off!

165
00:12:28,152 --> 00:12:31,246
The weak can't survive
if they don't support each other.

166
00:12:32,123 --> 00:12:35,820
So they trust people easily
and are betrayed.

167
00:12:36,594 --> 00:12:40,291
Weaklings like you guys
should just run about and away.

168
00:12:41,132 --> 00:12:43,032
Right, Idate?

169
00:12:44,235 --> 00:12:47,033
It was like that also
when you stole

170
00:12:47,105 --> 00:12:48,538
this Blade of the Thunder God, right?

171
00:12:55,580 --> 00:12:58,606
I can see it.
That's the Village Hidden in the Rain.

172
00:13:01,986 --> 00:13:02,884
Aoi Sensei?!

173
00:13:07,325 --> 00:13:08,349
Aoi Sensei!

174
00:13:11,596 --> 00:13:12,221
Idate...

175
00:13:12,764 --> 00:13:14,095
B-Big Brother...

176
00:13:14,932 --> 00:13:16,126
You idiot!

177
00:13:16,868 --> 00:13:19,098
Go back to the village immediately
and surrender yourself!

178
00:13:21,439 --> 00:13:22,337
You?!

179
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:25,873
Do you know what
you have done?

180
00:13:28,179 --> 00:13:28,873
What?!

181
00:13:31,883 --> 00:13:35,979
Strict as always, eh?
And he's your cute little brother.

182
00:13:36,587 --> 00:13:40,455
But it's truly perfect that
you've shown up here.

183
00:13:41,392 --> 00:13:42,620
Aoi Sensei...

184
00:13:43,561 --> 00:13:45,529
This forbidden Jutsu scroll
can't be deciphered

185
00:13:45,596 --> 00:13:48,030
unless you're Jonin class.

186
00:13:48,599 --> 00:13:51,534
I'll have the brothers
betray the Leaf Village together.

187
00:14:08,386 --> 00:14:11,753
Ibiki, please decipher it already.

188
00:14:12,490 --> 00:14:13,514
I refuse.

189
00:14:14,058 --> 00:14:17,550
So are you choosing death,
together with Idate?

190
00:14:20,198 --> 00:14:22,325
Such as he is,
he's also a Shinobi.

191
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:25,335
He's not afraid of death.

192
00:14:28,673 --> 00:14:30,766
It doesn't seem so.

193
00:14:31,576 --> 00:14:34,067
This face is one taut with fear.

194
00:14:36,047 --> 00:14:40,416
I'm quitting as a Ninja!
So please don't kill me!

195
00:14:41,018 --> 00:14:43,179
Please decipher it.

196
00:14:43,454 --> 00:14:46,218
You don't want to see
your cute little brother killed

197
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:48,053
before your eyes, do you?

198
00:14:49,093 --> 00:14:50,458
Little brother, you say?

199
00:14:51,429 --> 00:14:52,862
That fool?

200
00:14:53,764 --> 00:14:54,560
Big Brother...

201
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:58,764
Such a threat means nothing to me.

202
00:15:01,939 --> 00:15:05,568
Hey, Ibiki, is the Village Hidden
in the Leaves that important?

203
00:15:07,812 --> 00:15:09,803
Even if you protect it at
the risk of your own life,

204
00:15:10,014 --> 00:15:12,244
you're nothing but a pawn!

205
00:15:13,918 --> 00:15:15,943
So that's why
you became a traitor?

206
00:15:17,488 --> 00:15:18,853
You're a pathetic man!

207
00:15:19,757 --> 00:15:21,349
You punk!

208
00:15:34,505 --> 00:15:35,130
Idate!

209
00:15:36,474 --> 00:15:37,463
You, run away!

210
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:40,172
What about you, Big Brother?

211
00:15:40,545 --> 00:15:42,706
I'll go, after I clean up
the mess here!

212
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,479
I don't think so!

213
00:15:53,858 --> 00:15:54,688
Big Brother!

214
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,322
Go, quickly!

215
00:15:57,261 --> 00:15:58,489
But Big Brother...!

216
00:15:58,729 --> 00:16:01,562
Go! Having you stay is a burden!

217
00:16:05,503 --> 00:16:06,527
I won't let you!

218
00:16:07,338 --> 00:16:08,100
Go!

219
00:16:39,737 --> 00:16:41,068
So appalling...

220
00:16:41,672 --> 00:16:45,005
that he'd risk
his life for such an idiotic guy.

221
00:16:45,643 --> 00:16:48,339
All you could do after that
was run.

222
00:16:49,013 --> 00:16:52,039
You could've returned
to the village and called for help.

223
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,242
But you didn't do that.

224
00:16:55,386 --> 00:16:59,880
Thinking Ibiki was dead
was no excuse!

225
00:17:00,558 --> 00:17:02,389
The fact is, he was alive...

226
00:17:03,527 --> 00:17:05,859
In that regard,
Ibiki was admirable.

227
00:17:06,497 --> 00:17:09,432
Not only did he completely endure
repeated interrogation,

228
00:17:09,734 --> 00:17:11,929
but he also retrieved
the Forbidden Jutsu scroll...

229
00:17:12,436 --> 00:17:15,337
without having confessed to anything

230
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:21,334
And to think that he did
all this

231
00:17:21,412 --> 00:17:24,848
for his good for nothing little brother.

232
00:17:26,183 --> 00:17:29,380
You betrayed your village,
abandoned your older brother,

233
00:17:29,453 --> 00:17:31,944
and came to think of only yourself.

234
00:17:33,624 --> 00:17:38,391
Even Ibiki who is blood-related
and risked his life to save you,

235
00:17:38,529 --> 00:17:40,588
you didn't trust him!

236
00:17:41,832 --> 00:17:43,891
Afraid of being accused,

237
00:17:44,135 --> 00:17:48,037
you didn't trust the Village Hidden
in the Leaves, your birthplace...

238
00:17:48,873 --> 00:17:50,204
You trust nobody.

239
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:53,301
You're not trusted by anyone.

240
00:17:54,478 --> 00:17:58,073
For me, there is no pupil
as excellent as you.

241
00:17:59,216 --> 00:18:01,776
As a reward,
I'll let you die in one instant.

242
00:18:08,659 --> 00:18:09,387
Idate!

243
00:18:09,994 --> 00:18:11,723
Sasuke... Sakura!

244
00:18:12,296 --> 00:18:13,923
Rest, Naruto!

245
00:18:14,699 --> 00:18:16,633
I'll beat this guy!

246
00:18:18,736 --> 00:18:20,533
Don't be acting cool, believe it.

247
00:18:21,105 --> 00:18:24,506
You can't beat me, no matter
how many people show up.

248
00:18:25,476 --> 00:18:27,137
Me, Aoi Rokusho,

249
00:18:27,211 --> 00:18:31,204
the Rain Jonin who possesses
the Blade of the Thunder God.

250
00:18:32,016 --> 00:18:32,846
Is that so?

251
00:18:35,152 --> 00:18:36,676
Interesting.

252
00:18:37,121 --> 00:18:39,749
The Blade of the Thunder God
and my Chidori!

253
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:43,518
Let's test which is better!

254
00:18:57,942 --> 00:18:59,876
The rumors were true.

255
00:19:00,377 --> 00:19:03,676
The survivor of the village's honorable
Uchiha Clan...

256
00:19:03,748 --> 00:19:06,012
is just a good for nothing kid...

257
00:19:12,323 --> 00:19:13,119
Sasuke!

258
00:19:13,491 --> 00:19:14,583
Run, Sakura!

259
00:19:14,859 --> 00:19:16,793
He'll show no mercy,
no matter who the person is.

260
00:19:16,861 --> 00:19:18,488
Everyone will be killed!

261
00:19:19,230 --> 00:19:20,060
No way!

262
00:19:20,598 --> 00:19:21,223
Huh?!

263
00:19:21,499 --> 00:19:23,228
We'll protect you,
no matter what.

264
00:19:23,601 --> 00:19:24,966
We promised that, didn't we?!

265
00:19:25,803 --> 00:19:26,963
Trust us!

266
00:19:27,905 --> 00:19:30,237
Now all that's left is
the wounded rabbit

267
00:19:30,307 --> 00:19:32,502
and the excellent pupil, huh?

268
00:19:33,744 --> 00:19:36,770
You two together,
go to the next world.

269
00:19:38,983 --> 00:19:39,972
Take it back!

270
00:19:42,653 --> 00:19:43,642
Take it back!

271
00:19:45,122 --> 00:19:46,316
What're you talking about?

272
00:19:47,057 --> 00:19:48,081
What you said...

273
00:19:49,126 --> 00:19:50,457
earlier!

274
00:19:52,429 --> 00:19:54,158
Don't mess...

275
00:19:55,199 --> 00:19:56,598
with the Uchiha...

276
00:19:57,334 --> 00:19:58,892
with me!

277
00:20:06,143 --> 00:20:08,407
Why you!

278
00:20:33,804 --> 00:20:34,600
Sasuke!

279
00:20:39,043 --> 00:20:40,271
Sasuke! Get up!

280
00:20:41,312 --> 00:20:44,679
How very cold the bottom
of the ocean must be.

281
00:20:44,748 --> 00:20:46,272
Stop!

282
00:20:48,118 --> 00:20:48,846
Idate!

283
00:20:55,526 --> 00:20:56,356
Sakura!

284
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:04,094
Sakura!

285
00:21:12,610 --> 00:21:19,709
<i>Once in a long while, once in a while</i>

286
00:21:19,884 --> 00:21:25,413
<i>The remnants of a person</i>
<i>broken by dreams</i>

287
00:21:25,589 --> 00:21:30,652
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

288
00:21:33,964 --> 00:21:40,961
<i>Clinging to the Divine,</i>
<i>clinging to Buddha</i>

289
00:21:41,038 --> 00:21:46,567
<i>The remnants of a person crying</i>

290
00:21:46,977 --> 00:21:50,538
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

291
00:21:52,216 --> 00:21:55,276
<i>Rendezvous with a happy dance circle</i>

292
00:21:55,352 --> 00:21:59,152
<i>This is my victory pose, round and around</i>
<i>(round around)</i>

293
00:21:59,490 --> 00:22:02,425
<i>Shake shake shake</i>
<i>Let's look</i>

294
00:22:02,493 --> 00:22:06,623
<i>With a bye bye rhythm that never ends</i>

295
00:22:15,806 --> 00:22:20,903
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

296
00:22:22,846 --> 00:22:26,111
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

297
00:22:26,517 --> 00:22:29,714
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

298
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:33,956
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

299
00:22:37,995 --> 00:22:39,690
What the heck should we do?

300
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:42,098
That sword of the Second Hokage
won't budge an inch

301
00:22:42,166 --> 00:22:46,034
even with Sasuke's Chidori
or my Rasengan!

302
00:22:46,537 --> 00:22:49,506
But I can't lose this battle.

303
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:51,464
I won't run away, no matter what!

304
00:22:52,009 --> 00:22:57,037
If my techniques aren't going to work,
I'll just have to keep trying!

305
00:22:58,215 --> 00:23:02,208
Next time: "The Last Leg:
A Final Act of Desperation"
